---
import Separator from '@core/components/ui/separator.astro'
import Layout from '@core/layouts/layout.astro'
import WithSidebar from '@core/layouts/with-sidebar.astro'
---
<Layout >
    <main class="flex flex-col gap-16">
        <WithSidebar>
            <section
                class="flex-1 flex flex-col gap-16 w-3/4"
                slot="content"
            >
                <section class="flex flex-col gap-2 mb-8">
                    <h1 class="text-3xl font-medium">
                        Introduction
                    </h1>
                    <h3 class="text-3xl font-light">
                        Curated collection of components with minimalism in mind.
                    </h3>
                </section>

                <section id="about" class="flex flex-col gap-8">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="font-medium text-xl mb-2">This collection provides unique and specialized components that are not typically available out of the box.</h3>
                        <p>We do not claim to own all of the components or design, it's just recreated out of admiration of their work.</p>
                    </div>

                    <p>This is <span class="font-medium">NOT</span> a component library. It's a collection of re-usable components <span class="font-medium">inspired</span> by various designers that you can copy and paste into your projects. Built using tailwind.</p>

                    <Separator/>
                    <div>
                        <p class="font-medium text-xl mb-2">Yes, we also use <span class="underline"><a href="https://ui.shadcn.com/">shadcn</a></span>.</p>
                        <p>We are aware of the many UI and component libraries out there.</p>
                        <p>Our goal isn't to increase dependencies but, creating modular yet beautiful components as if you built it your own.</p>
                    </div>

                    <p class="font-medium">We refrain from using external dependencies unless needed, so you can fully customize all the components as you wish.</p>

                    <p class="italic">Use this as a reference or framework to build your own components</p>
                </section> 
                <Separator/>
                <section>
                    <h3 class="font-medium text-xl mb-2">Supported frameworks or libraries</h3>
                    <p>Yes, everything is built with tailwind</p>
                    <p>Anything that works with React probably.&nbsp;<span class="font-medium underline">React</span>, <span class="font-medium underline">Next.js</span>, <span class="font-medium underline">Astro</span> for now.</p>
                </section>
            </section>
            
        </WithSidebar>
    </main>
</Layout>


